  "title": "docs(review): complete docs review",
  "body": "- /guide/ and /examples/ instead of /guide.html /examples.html so that\r\nif you are on /guide/Installation.html and try to go on /guide/, it\r\nworks\r\n- moved advanced topics at the root of the guide\r\n- reorganized the guide so it follows a progressive learning path\r\n- read the guide entirely and made adjustement as if I was a new\r\nuser/reader\r\n- made small adjustements on the rendering\r\n- removed the need for @kind + @category, only kept @kind\r\n(InstantSearch component is OK as a widget, it's not really a widget\r\nbut 90% of our components are widgets so it's easier to only talk\r\nabout widgets for users given the current shape of the API navigation)\r\n- removed headings left navigation BUT from the getting started, pages are too small\r\nto have headings (and sometime repetitive headings). Did not feel the\r\npain not having them, reduces noise\r\n\r\nI have other ideas how to make the docs better, will bring them to\r\ndiscuss once we are live. Right now we should be safe for a first\r\nrelease **content wise** (we still have small adjustements/fine tuning to do).\r\n\r\n![new-docs](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/20862679/d5391092-b9b1-11e6-83e5-e9ad392e19bf.gif)\r\n",
